Pictures don’t do it justice, but we had the best night at El Rey Del Pescado in Sunset Park last night. Every bite was fresh and outstanding. I can’t stop thinking about the crab empanada, my mezcal guava cocktail, & octopus taco. We also had a fried seafood platter with the homemade salsas and wished we could buy the bottles of their salsas. For dessert we had coconut flan and chocolate empanadas with homemade ice cream. From the tortillas to the fish to the icecream everything was so fresh and the highest quality. To top it all off the ambience was incredible- beautiful spacious back patio, great music, super accommodating kind staff. Can’t wait to go back. — ￼eating dinner at El Rey Del Pescado.

I had a seafood platter and a fish taco and shrimp taco. Everything was so fresh even the tortillas. Cocktail was delicious and beautiful! They have a huge back patio very spacious. Owner and staff super friendly. So glad I went in!!! Check them out.

Rodger the owner is kind and attentive he always goes the extra mile for his customers! Edgar the lead server is amazing in every way! The food is amazing get the shrimp empinadas if you know what's good,  although knowing me I highly recommend the drinks made by irena she is a true  mixologist  The inside of the place is decorated well with a new age maritime theme. The court yard has been modified for year round dining and is comfortable anytime of the year.  Overall a great experience would and will come again!  Do yourself a favor and ask for edgar by name if you want great service!!

This is my first time in this restaurant. Usually I'm not looking for a sea food restaurant because it's very difficult to have a great experience in NY (I'm from Baja and my wife is from Sinaloa that means I have a really high expectations for the sea food) but we came here today and wooooow 😛😛😛 100% real mexican taste in every dish. We ordered some tacos, one of chile poblano relleno, shrimp and octopus all with hand made tortillas 👌👌 full of flavors, then some octopus tostadas, a shrimp cocktail and at the end an aguachile 😝.  In other words ... one of the best or I can say the best sea food restaurant in New York!!!! You won't be disappointed but as a note all the dishes takes a little time to arrive to your table because the are made entirely when you place the order even the tortillas, so please be patient and you will have a great experience.
